						<div class="postbody">The really weird thing is that it's not constant from scanline to scanline. The source of interference is somewhere around 1.35MHz or so... That strongly implies the interference is not from inside the NES, because everything inside is running from the same clock.<br /><br />Did you move your NES physically around the room after those couple days?</div>

